<h1>Neuros</h1>
<p>Imperial House Neuros overthrew House Corvanimus for power in 741 CR. Since then it has played a dangerous game of "balancing the pawns." It has fueled enmity among the other houses, trying to insure that with all the infighting no other House could grow strong enough to rival Neuros. However, the houses are beginning to get wise to Neuros' tricks. These days Neuros walks a thin line of control indeed.</p>
<h2>Ranks</h2>
<ul>
<li>Capriarch</li>
<li>Suzerain</li>
<li>Cousin</li>
</ul>
<h2>Perk Bonuses</h2>
<p>Only humans who have chosen Chrysanthia as their home region may choose this House. Selecting this house is only available at character creation. However, characters who select House Scion(Neuros 1) at creation can take further ranks at any time.</p>
<h3>House Scion(1)</h3>
<p>Your character is one of the lucky few to have been born into the family also known as House Neuros. Everyone in Chrysanthia knows the character is a member of House Neuros. They are treated with respect, though sometimes grudgingly, and few are willing to cross them. However, with the power of high birth comes the the responsibilities of position. They gain the benefits of Reputation(1) with anyone that has ever spent at least a week on Chrysanthia. They gain the benefits of Contacts (House Neuros 1) when travelling Chrysanthia. Once every month they are susceptible to the flaw Owed Favor(1).</p>
